        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 8:22PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 821 PM MDT/921 PM CDT/, the public reported gusty showers along a
line extending from 14 miles north of Goodland to 9 miles north of
Brewster. Movement was northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bird City.

This includes Interstate 70 in Kansas between mile markers 1 and 49.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT/1100
PM CDT/ for northwestern Kansas.</instruction>
